title: Juanita-Sammamish high school football game on Oct. 2. cancelled
text:
Juanita-Sammamish high school football game on Oct. 2. cancelled Originally published October 2, 2015 at 7:18 pm Totems cannot safely field a team due to low numbers. By Solange Reyner 
The Juanita-Sammamish KingCo 3A/2A football game set for tonight, Oct. 2, has been cancelled because Sammamish cannot safely field a team due to low numbers. 
Sammamish played Bellevue last Friday and lost, 47-7. The Totems also had to forfeit last year’s game against Juanita because they did not have enough players. 
Here’s what Juanita athletic director Steve Juzeler sent out on Friday morning: “Juanita Family- We would like to inform you that the Juanita/Sammamish varsity football game scheduled for 7pm this evening has been cancelled. Due to low numbers, Sammamish cannot safely field a team. Sportsmanship and safety are priorities at Juanita and we support their decision in these unfortunate circumstances. Once a Rebel, Always a Rebel.”
